timeline.bodyText:
Could we create a StorageUploadInputStreamOptions class to use here instead?   For now, they will have the exact same set of options, but a distinct class will allow them to diverge in the future if needed.
To avoid code duplication, you could create a common superclass StorageUploadOptions, which is extended by StorageUploadFileOptions and StorageUploadInputStreamOptions, like this:
public class StorageUploadOptions extends StorageOptions {
    private final String contentType;
    private final Map<String, String> metadata;
}

public class StorageUploadFileOptions extends StorageUploadOptions { }
public class StorageUploadInputStreamOptions extends StorageUploadOptions { }

